Tips to draw people💃🕺✍🏻😊 I like to use dots to mark the body parts that help me balance proportions. Sometimes I place 3 dots dividing figure into 2 parts but here I use 4 dots to mark shoulders, elbows, top of the knees and ankles. I find it easier to start with drawing people walking away, minimum details, focusing on proportions. Shadows add some realism and ground the figures. Give it a try!
